Suprabranchial pores 2 (
Burke 1930
).

Pectoral fin deeply notched, with 32 rays (Tables 2–3 ). Upper lobe 65.3 % HL, with 24 rays extending beyond anus to anal-fin origin. Lower lobe moderately elongate,> 34.3 % SL, with 8 rays, extending to anus (
Burke 1930
). Uppermost pectoral-fin ray level with oral cleft. Insertion of lowermost pectoral-fin ray below mid-orbit.

Prickles absent. Pyloric caeca 21 (
Burke 1930
).
